After treatment with rFeIFN-ω (at V2 and for the subsequent 6 months), an evident clinical improvement was observed in all sick treated cats, especially those with a clinical score (CS) of ≥6 (Table 1
). Such an improvement was not observed in untreated cats (p
 < 0.05). Asymptomatic cats or those with mild disease remained stable. This clinical improvement agrees with data from De Mari et al. (2004) and from studies with rHuIFN-α (Pedretti et al., 2006). One treated and one untreated-FeLV+ cat, each with very severe initial disease (CS = 10 and CS = 8, respectively) died between V1 and V2.
